CS 227 - Windows 7 install
	Delete all non-OS partitions off both disks
		Don't delete the partition containing XP!
	Convert the disk that does NOT contain XP to basic
		The windows install process cannot install on a dynamic disk
	Configure BIOS to boot off optical drive first, followed by hard drive
	Reboot off Windows 7 disk
		Create a 50GB partition to hold Windows 7
		Install on that partition
		Answer prompts reasonably
	Boot up XP to verify it still works
	Boot up 7 to verify it works
		Turn off automatic updates!
		Install Motherboard drivers off driver CD
